To avoid this, you have to thread one through the front of your ear first (on the left side) and the second through the back (on the right ear). If you do this one teardrop points forward, the other points back but the stamp is not visible.

It's a soft pliable metal so they're easy to put in but gentle care is necessary. You can see I misshaped one trying to figure out why they weren't hanging the opposite/mirrored. title: This is by far the best workout headband/sweatband I have ever worn
text: This is by far the best workout headband/sweatband I have ever worn.  It's not 100% slip proof, but it's the closest thing I have encountered. When I resumed my workout sweat was rushing down my face and that's when I realized what an excellent job the headband was doing from keeping sweat away.  It is completely sweat proof.  I decided to put the headband back on, but I wore it lower on my forehead.  It stayed on for the remainder of my 1.5 hour workout.  The only time it doesn't stay in place for me is when I do jumping jacks.  I have worn this while running, Zumba, spin, shred.  If I need to adjust the headband I can do so without the headband bringing my hair forward on my face like other sweatbands.  The closure system on the headband allows for this.  I decided to order a GreecieGirl Headband because they have cute prints and so many rave reviews.  They may have a bigger selection to choose from, but they don't their job.  It didn't even feel secure.  Qwickband feels secure without being tight.  The Qwickband did a far superior job of staying in place and wicking away sweat. I've washed it several times and it still looks and feels brand new.  I will definitely order another Qwickband.

title: A great way to get started with solid cologne
text: These were my first actual purchase of solid cologne. I liked the idea of getting a sample pack and I wish more companies had items like this. Along with the variety, what I also like is that the base of these seem generally safe or "natural" in that its almond oil and a shea butter base with some fragrance. The sizes are convenient, too, to keep one at work or at the gym (I would say the car, too, but the change in temperatures in your car might not be good for this product). I like being able to rub these on pulse points rather than spray a cloud of cologne. Yes, the scent is more subtle because you are not spraying it so it seems as if it doesn't last long; however, I recommend rubbing it not just on the wrists but up the arm a bit so that it is less likely to wash off when you wash your hands. Cologne is meant to be subtle, anyway, in order to draw someone in rather than repel them. I'd give this 5 stars if the fragrances were just a bit less like traditional cologne. By that, I mean that there are some cleaner scents out there; however, I did notice that once these were on my skin and mixed with my body chemistry that they seemed less like the sharp scent of a chemical-y cologne and more natural.

The only thing I might have done differently is to maybe choose a less "scripty" font for her name, since it came out so little. If it had filled up more of the tag, it would have been better.
